OL,3,CFood parcels hit record numbers, as
OL,4,Cpeople 'unable to afford essentials.'
OL,6,F"Everyone in Wales should be able to
OL,7,Fafford the essentials ` to buy their
OL,8,Fown food and heat their homes. This
OL,9,Fhas got harder in the last year, as
OL,10,Fhas been shown by the 47,700 people
OL,11,Fneeding an emergency food parcel for
OL,12,Fthe first time. This is not right.
OL,13,FSomething has to change.
OL,15,F"The new First Minister must work to
OL,16,Fend the need for food banks in Wales.
OL,17,FWith a new child poverty strategy in
OL,18,Fplace and a commitment to streamline
OL,19,FWelsh benefits, the Welsh Government
OL,20,Fhas levers to turn the tide of
OL,21,Fhardship facing our communities.
